noun
plural A levels
[count] Brit :an advanced test in a particular subject that students in England, Wales, and Northern Ireland take usually at the age of
The university requires at least three A levels.
She got an A in her A levels in maths, physics, and chemistry. - called also Advanced level, - compare o level, s level

(khẩu ngữ) x Advanced level;
When are you taking A level (you're a level)?
Khi nào thì anh lấy bằng A?
